import hummuspasta from '../assets/hummuspasta.png';
import vns from '../assets/vns.png';
import gs from '../assets/greensmoothie.png';
import vietnoodlesalad from '../assets/vietnoodlesalad.png';

export const RecipeList = [
    {
        "name": "Hummus Pasta",
        "image": hummuspasta,
        "time": "20 minutes",
        "link":"/hummuspasta",
        "desc": 'A simple and tasty meal perfect for college students or people on the go. Only takes under 30 minutes to prepare and can be made into leftovers - just as good or even better the day after!',
        "ingredients":[
            "4 cups whole wheat pasta (gf pasta for gfo)",
            "4 tablespoons hummus","1 lemon's juice",
            "2 cups your choice of vegetables","a pinch of salt and pepper"
        ],
        "instructions":[
            "Boil pasta according to package instructions.",
            "Boil vegetables in the last minute.",
            "Drain pasta and vegetables and put them back into the same pot.",
            "Turn the heat down to medium and add the hummus, lemon juice, and salt and pepper.",
            "Stir until thoroughly combined. Taste and season as needed."
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "Veg Noodle Soup",
        "image": vns,
        "time": "20 minutes",
        "link":"/vegnoodlesoup",
        "desc": 'A quick nourishing meal to get your veggies, vitamins, and fiber in. Perfect for a rainy day or any day that you just need a warm hug.',
        "ingredients":[
            "4 cups whole wheat pasta (gf pasta for gfo)",
            "6 cups of vegetable broth",
            "1 tablespoon of soy sauce",
            "2 cups frozen mixed vegetables",
            "1/4 tsp ground black pepper"
        ],
        "instructions":[
            "Boil pasta according to package instructions using the vegetable broth.",
            "Boil vegetables in the last minute.",
            "Add in soy sauce and let simmer for 3-5 minutes.",
            "Crack black pepper in and season to taste.",
            "Add in your choice of toppings (cilantro, scallions, etc)."
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "Green Smoothie",
        "image": gs,
        "time": "7 minutes",
        "link":"/greensmoothie",
        "desc": 'A bright smoothie filled with greens, fiber, protein, and fat. A perfect on-the-go meal for breakfast, lunch, snack, or even dinner!',
        "ingredients":[
            "1 frozen banana","1 cup almond milk",
            "1 scoop vanilla plant-based protein powder",
            "1 tablespoon almond butter",
            "1 cup of spinach, packed",
            "Handful of ice cubes"
          ],
        "instructions":[
            "Add almond milk to blender first, and then protein powder to prevent sticking.",
            "Add banana, ice, and almond butter to blender.",
            "Use a spinach leaf to wipe off all almond butter from spoon for easy clean up.",
            "Add in rest of spinach.",
            "Blend until no clumps left or until desired consistency.",
            "Pour into a glass, top with desired toppings (optional: hempseeds, chia seeds, etc) and enjoy!"
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "Vietnamese Noodle Salad",
        "image": vietnoodlesalad,
        "time": "30 minutes",
        "link":"/vietnoodlesalad",
        "desc": "A refreshing yet nourshing salad perfect for the hot weather! A combination of crunchy vegetables, chewy noodles, and baked tofu is sure to leave you feeling refreshed & satisfied!",
